Validation query
Note written on 2 March 2026.

The following is a query sent by Brian Gelsinger on 10.31.2025.

This was meant to be a validation set restricted in scope to a single department
in order to inform the development of the "brute force" algorithm to estimate headcount.

As of 2 March 2026, it has not been used due to re-organization and shifting priorities.

Copying from the email message: 

Hi Bill,

Attached is the SQL for job data as of 01/01 and 07/01 of each year from 2020 to current for employees in Dept ID 00055 Chemical Engineering as of the snapshot dates.

Also, after reviewing the original SQL that was provided, I did confirm that Hospital employees were included.

Let me know if you have any questions, and have a great weekend.

Thanks!




SELECT DISTINCT B.AS_OF_DATE, A.EMPLID, C.NAME, A.EMPL_RCD
    , A.FTE
    , A.JOBCODE, D.DESCR JOBTITLE
    , A.DEPTID, CASE WHEN E.DEPTID IS NULL THEN 'INACTIVE' ELSE E.DEPTNAME END DEPT_NAME
    , CASE WHEN  D.UU_BEN_IND = '01' OR  A.JOBCODE IN ('6001', '6002', '6003', '6004', '6005', '6102', '6103', '6104', '6105') THEN 'Faculty' ELSE 'Staff' END FACULTY_FLAG
    , CASE WHEN SUM( A.FTE) OVER (PARTITION BY  A.EMPLID, B.AS_OF_DATE)>= .75 THEN 'Full-Time' ELSE 'Part-Time' END FULL_TIME_STATUS
    , H.HIRE_DT, H.REHIRE_DT,H.TERMINATION_DT, H.SERVICE_DT
    
FROM PS_JOB A
    
    JOIN 
    (SELECT DISTINCT TO_DATE(
      (EXTRACT(YEAR FROM BD.HIRE_DT) 
      || '-'
      ||Case when EXTRACT(MONTH FROM BD.HIRE_DT) < 10
          then '0'||EXTRACT(MONTH FROM BD.HIRE_DT)
          else TO_CHAR(EXTRACT(MONTH FROM BD.HIRE_DT)) end
      ||'-01')
      ,'YYYY-MM-DD') AS_OF_DATE
FROM PS_UU_EMPLOYMENT BD
WHERE (BD.HIRE_DT BETWEEN (SYSDATE-2190) AND SYSDATE) 
ORDER BY TO_DATE(
      (EXTRACT(YEAR FROM BD.HIRE_DT) 
      || '-'
      ||Case when EXTRACT(MONTH FROM BD.HIRE_DT) < 10
          then '0'||EXTRACT(MONTH FROM BD.HIRE_DT)
          else TO_CHAR(EXTRACT(MONTH FROM BD.HIRE_DT)) end
      ||'-01')
      ,'YYYY-MM-DD')) B
  

        ON (A.EFFDT <= B.AS_OF_DATE)
    
    
    JOIN PS_PERSON_NAME C
        ON (C.EMPLID = A.EMPLID)
    JOIN PS_JOBCODE_TBL D
        ON (D.JOBCODE = A.JOBCODE)
    LEFT OUTER JOIN HRBI_2023_TREE_TBL E
        ON (E.DEPTID = A.DEPTID)
    JOIN PS_UU_EMPLOYMENT H
        ON (H.EMPLID = A.EMPLID)
   

WHERE SUBSTR(B.AS_OF_DATE,4,3)IN ('JUL','JAN')
    AND A.EMPL_STATUS IN ('A', 'L', 'P', 'S', 'W')
    AND A.DEPTID NOT IN ('00824', '00825', '00826', '00827', '01144', '01147', '90139') -- Benefit's Only Depts
    AND A.JOBCODE NOT IN ('9229', '9230', '9233', '9234', '9235', '9238', '9239', '9240', '9241', '9243', '9244', '9250', '9254', '9256', '9257', '7993') -- Benefit's Only Job Codes
    AND A.DEPTID = '00055'     
    
    AND A.EFFDT = (SELECT MAX(A_ED.EFFDT)--Job as of DATE
        FROM PS_JOB A_ED
        WHERE A.EMPLID = A_ED.EMPLID
        AND A.EMPL_RCD = A_ED.EMPL_RCD
        AND A_ED.EFFDT <= B.AS_OF_DATE)
    AND A.EFFSEQ = (SELECT MAX(A_ES.EFFSEQ)
        FROM PS_JOB A_ES
        WHERE A.EMPLID = A_ES.EMPLID
        AND A.EMPL_RCD = A_ES.EMPL_RCD
        AND A.EFFDT = A_ES.EFFDT)--max effseq
    AND D.EFFDT = (SELECT MAX(D_ED.EFFDT)
        FROM PS_JOBCODE_TBL D_ED
        WHERE D.JOBCODE = D_ED.JOBCODE
        AND D_ED.EFFDT <= SYSDATE)-- Job code data as of SYSDATE
 

ORDER BY B.AS_OF_DATE, A.EMPLID, A.EMPL_RCD